         <abstract>
            <p>This record refers to the collection of prayers to the Trinity for each day of the week
               (<ref type="work" corresp="LIT2296Sayfas"/>) together with miracles either following the prayer
            for each day one by one or following the prayers as a whole.</p>
            <p>This work is different from <ref type="work" corresp="LIT2281Trinity"/> (a collection of miracles of the Trinity attributed
               to <persName ref="PRS2748BeduaA"/>) and from
               <ref type="work" corresp="LIT2282Trinity"/> (a collection of miracles of the 
               Trinity transmitted with <ref type="work" corresp="LIT1300Dersan"/>).</p>
            <p>   From     <bibl>
               <ptr target="bm:Nosnitsin2010EAETammeraS"/>
            </bibl> (minimally rephrased): A collection of miracles worked
            by the Trinity, in which
            a wondrous story follows a homily, for each
            day of the week. One of the types of the collections known as the <ref type="work" corresp="LIT2388Taamme">Miracles of the Trinity</ref>
            </p>
         
         </abstract>
